AGENT AxiomAutoTrainPrep
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Convert AXIOM training data to HuggingFace AutoTrain format
GOAL Transform instruction-output examples into chat-formatted text
     Augment thin categories with diagnostic variants
     Produce CSV and JSONL ready for direct AutoTrain upload

RECEIVES training_data: jsonl, format: string, augment: bool
EMITS train_csv: file, train_jsonl: file, stats: dict, validation: dict
MUTATES examples_list, augmented_list, converted_list
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, trust_level, system_prompt, quality_thresholds, dedup_method

CONSTRAINT Every example must pass quality filter before conversion
CONSTRAINT Output shorter than thirty characters is excluded
CONSTRAINT Output longer than eight thousand characters is excluded
CONSTRAINT Empty instructions are excluded
CONSTRAINT Deduplication by instruction hash applied after augmentation
CONSTRAINT System prompt is injected into every training example
CONSTRAINT No secrets or API keys in training output

RULES
- Load source examples from axiom_training_data.jsonl
- Apply quality filter to remove short, long, and empty examples
- Augment bug_fix examples with a diagnosis variant
- Augment spec_explanation examples with a constraints variant
- Deduplicate all examples by MD5 hash of instruction
- Convert each example using the selected format converter
- Write CSV with single text column for AutoTrain
- Write JSONL as alternative upload format
- Report example count, character total, estimated tokens, and file size
- Show type breakdown after conversion

PROCESS
- Load source JSONL file line by line
- Apply quality filter: minimum thirty chars, maximum eight thousand, non-empty instruction
- On augmentation enabled, generate variants for bug_fix and spec_explanation types
- Deduplicate by instruction hash
- Convert each example to selected chat format with system prompt
- Write autotrain_data/train.csv with text column header
- Write autotrain_data/train.jsonl as alternative
- Calculate and display statistics

CHECK
- All examples have non-empty text after conversion
- CSV has text column header
- No rows under one hundred characters in final output
- Estimated token count is within model context limits
- Deduplication removed actual duplicates
- Augmented count exceeds source count

FAILURE
- On missing source file: report and suggest running dataset builder first
- On zero examples after filter: report quality threshold issue
- On format not recognized: fall back to ChatML

OUTPUT
- autotrain_data/train.csv: single text column, one chat-formatted example per row
- autotrain_data/train.jsonl: one JSON object per line with text field
- Statistics: row count, total characters, estimated tokens, file sizes
- Validation: column check, empty row check, length distribution

SUCCESS
coverage: 0.30
format_quality: 0.30
augmentation: 0.20
upload_ready: 0.20
